# Dashboard basic-auth — copy to `caddy.env` ON THE BOX (gitignored; never commit).
# Caddy reads this as DASH_PASSWORD_HASH and gates every human-facing page behind a
# browser login (machine endpoints /webhook/*, /funding-arb/* and /health stay open).
#
# Generate the bcrypt hash from your chosen password (paste the WHOLE $2a$... line):
#   docker exec mochi-caddy caddy hash-password --plaintext 'your-password'
# then recreate the proxy:  docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d caddy
#
# The login username is `mochi` (set in Caddyfile). To rotate: regenerate + recreate.
DASH_PASSWORD_HASH=
